                    },
                    "body": "So if the table has a single dictionary column, it hangs. But when there are also other columns, eg with this dataframe (rest of the code is the same):\r\n\r\n{code:python}\r\ndf = pd.DataFrame({'a': range(20), 'b': pd.Categorical(['a', 'b']*10)})\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nit doesn't hang but gives an error:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nArrowInvalid: Column 1 named b expected length 0 but got length 20\r\n{code}",
